  "prompt": "Will yongnuo RF 603 ii RF triggers allows High speed sync triggering?",
  "response": "The Yongnuo RF-603 II triggers do not support high-speed sync (HSS) functionality. These triggers are designed for basic remote firing of flashes and provide basic synchronization at standard shutter speeds, typically up to 1/200s or 1/250s depending on the camera. \n\nIf you need high-speed sync capabilities, you would need to look into other triggers, such as the Yongnuo YN-622 series or Yongnuo YN-E3-RT, which support HSS for faster shutter speeds. Always verify device specifications based on the most recent information or user manuals from the manufacturer before making a decision.",
